          </div>
          <div class="card-stat"><span class="num">8</span><span class="cap">weeks · Novice 5K</span></div>
        </div>
        <h3>Hal Higdon</h3>
        <p>
          Veteran American coach and long-time Runner's World writer. His own Novice 5K plan is
          also 8 weeks with 3 runs per week and explicitly allows walk breaks — as he puts it,
          no rule says you have to run continuously.
        </p>
        <a class="card-source" href="https://www.halhigdon.com/training-programs/5k-training/novice-5k/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source: halhigdon.com ↗</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <div class="card-head">
          <div class="icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M19 14c1.49-1.46 3-3.21 3-5.5A5.5 5.5 0 0 0 16.5 3c-1.76 0-3 .5-4.5 2-1.5-1.5-2.74-2-4.5-2A5.5 5.5 0 0 0 2 8.5c0 2.29 1.49 4.04 3 5.5l7 7Z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="card-stat"><span class="num">9</span><span class="cap">weeks · 3× / week</span></div>
        </div>
        <h3>NHS Couch to 5K</h3>
        <p>
          The UK National Health Service's official free programme for beginners. Same philosophy
          as ours: 9 weeks, 3 workouts a week, gradually alternating running and walking up to
          30 minutes of continuous running.
        </p>
        <a class="card-source" href="https://www.nhs.uk/better-health/get-active/get-running-with-couch-to-5k/couch-to-5k-running-plan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source: nhs.uk ↗</a>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="plan-note" style="margin-top:2rem;">
      <svg style="width:1em;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.15em;margin-right:0.3em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M19 14c1.49-1.46 3-3.21 3-5.5A5.5 5.5 0 0 0 16.5 3c-1.76 0-3 .5-4.5 2-1.5-1.5-2.74-2-4.5-2A5.5 5.5 0 0 0 2 8.5c0 2.29 1.49 4.04 3 5.5l7 7Z"/></svg><strong>Did you know?</strong> In a study of more than 55,000 adults
      (<em>Journal of the American College of Cardiology</em>, 2014), runners — even those running
      just 5–10 minutes a day, even slowly — had a 30% lower risk of death and lived on average
      3 years longer than non-runners — a finding confirmed in 2020 by a meta-analysis of
      232,000+ participants (<em>British Journal of Sports Medicine</em>). Every workout in
      this plan counts, from the very first week.
    </div>

